    <h2 id="why-echinacea">How Echinacea Supports Your Immune System</h2>

    <p>Echinacea is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family, native to North America and used for centuries by Indigenous peoples as a remedy for infections, wounds, and general illness. Modern pharmacological research has identified three primary categories of bioactive compounds in echinacea: alkylamides (which modulate immune cell activity and reduce inflammation), polysaccharides (which activate macrophages and natural killer cells), and cichoric acid (a powerful antioxidant that protects immune cells from oxidative damage). These compounds work synergistically to enhance both innate and adaptive immune responses.</p>

    <div class="key-stat">
